<TITLE> Khaleda mourns Wazed </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 8 (bdnews24.com)Opposition leader Khaleda Zia has condoled the death of prime minister Sheikh Hasina's husband Dr MA Wazed Miah. "I am deeply shocked at the demise of Dr MA Wazed Miah, husband of prime minister Sheikh Hasina." In a condolence message released on Saturday evening, Khaleda expressed her deepest sympathy to the bereaved family members. "As a talented and self-dedicated scientist, Wazed Miah contributed immensely to the development of science and technology of the country," the former prime minister said. "It will take a long time to fill up the vacuum caused by his death." Khaleda prayed for the salvation of the departed soul. "At the moment, I am sharing the sorrow of the prime minister and expressing my sympathy to other relatives of the deceased through her." Lauding Dr. Miah, she said, "He deserves a great praise and honour for his unique politeness and courtesy, and his righteousness and devotion to profession." bdne
